  26 def _resolve(name) -> ModuleType:
  27     """If name is a string, resolve to a module."""
  28     if hasattr(name, '__spec__'):
  29         return name
  30     return import_module(name)
  31 
  32 
  33 def _get_package(package) -> ModuleType:
  34     """Take a package name or module object and return the module.
  35 
  36     If a name, the module is imported.  If the resolved module
  37     object is not a package, raise an exception.
  38     """
  39     module = _resolve(package)
  40     if module.__spec__.submodule_search_locations is None:
  41         raise TypeError('{!r} is not a package'.format(package))
  42     return module
  43

  45 def _normalize_path(path) -> str:
  46     """Normalize a path by ensuring it is a string.
  47 
  48     If the resulting string contains path separators, an exception is raised.
  49     """
  50     str_path = str(path)
  51     parent, file_name = os.path.split(str_path)
  52     if parent:
  53         raise ValueError('{!r} must be only a file name'.format(path))
  54     return file_name
  55

  57 def _get_resource_reader(
  58         package: ModuleType) -> Optional[resources_abc.ResourceReader]:
  59     # Return the package's loader if it's a ResourceReader.  We can't use
  60     # a issubclass() check here because apparently abc.'s __subclasscheck__()
  61     # hook wants to create a weak reference to the object, but
  62     # zipimport.zipimporter does not support weak references, resulting in a
  63     # TypeError.  That seems terrible.
  64     spec = package.__spec__
  65     reader = getattr(spec.loader, 'get_resource_reader', None)
  66     if reader is None:
  67         return None
  68     return cast(resources_abc.ResourceReader, reader(spec.name))

  71 def open_binary(package: Package, resource: Resource) -> BinaryIO:
  72     """Return a file-like object opened for binary reading of the resource."""
  73     resource = _normalize_path(resource)
  74     package = _get_package(package)
  75     reader = _get_resource_reader(package)
  76     if reader is not None:
  77         return reader.open_resource(resource)
  78     # Using pathlib doesn't work well here due to the lack of 'strict'
  79     # argument for pathlib.Path.resolve() prior to Python 3.6.
  80     absolute_package_path = os.path.abspath(
  81         package.__spec__.origin or 'non-existent file')
  82     package_path = os.path.dirname(absolute_package_path)
  83     full_path = os.path.join(package_path, resource)
  84     try:
  85         return open(full_path, mode='rb')
  86     except OSError:
  87         # Just assume the loader is a resource loader; all the relevant
  88         # importlib.machinery loaders are and an AttributeError for
  89         # get_data() will make it clear what is needed from the loader.
  90         loader = cast(ResourceLoader, package.__spec__.loader)
  91         data = None
  92         if hasattr(package.__spec__.loader, 'get_data'):
  93             with suppress(OSError):
  94                 data = loader.get_data(full_path)
  95         if data is None:
  96             package_name = package.__spec__.name
  97             message = '{!r} resource not found in {!r}'.format(
  98                 resource, package_name)
  99             raise FileNotFoundError(message)
 100         return BytesIO(data)

 103 def open_text(package: Package,
 104               resource: Resource,
 105               encoding: str = 'utf-8',
 106               errors: str = 'strict') -> TextIO:
 107     """Return a file-like object opened for text reading of the resource."""
 108     return TextIOWrapper(
 109         open_binary(package, resource), encoding=encoding, errors=errors)
 110 
 111 
 112 def read_binary(package: Package, resource: Resource) -> bytes:
 113     """Return the binary contents of the resource."""
 114     with open_binary(package, resource) as fp:
 115         return fp.read()
 116 
 117 
 118 def read_text(package: Package,
 119               resource: Resource,
 120               encoding: str = 'utf-8',
 121               errors: str = 'strict') -> str:
 122     """Return the decoded string of the resource.
 123 
 124     The decoding-related arguments have the same semantics as those of
 125     bytes.decode().
 126     """
 127     with open_text(package, resource, encoding, errors) as fp:
 128         return fp.read()

 131 def files(package: Package) -> resources_abc.Traversable:
 132     """
 133     Get a Traversable resource from a package
 134     """
 135     return _common.from_package(_get_package(package))

 138 def path(
 139         package: Package, resource: Resource,
 140         ) -> 'ContextManager[Path]':
 141     """A context manager providing a file path object to the resource.
 142 
 143     If the resource does not already exist on its own on the file system,
 144     a temporary file will be created. If the file was created, the file
 145     will be deleted upon exiting the context manager (no exception is
 146     raised if the file was deleted prior to the context manager
 147     exiting).
 148     """
 149     reader = _get_resource_reader(_get_package(package))
 150     return (
 151         _path_from_reader(reader, resource)
 152         if reader else
 153         _common.as_file(files(package).joinpath(_normalize_path(resource)))
 154         )
 155 
 156 
 157 @contextmanager
 158 def _path_from_reader(reader, resource):
 159     norm_resource = _normalize_path(resource)
 160     with suppress(FileNotFoundError):
 161         yield Path(reader.resource_path(norm_resource))
 162         return
 163     opener_reader = reader.open_resource(norm_resource)
 164     with _common._tempfile(opener_reader.read, suffix=norm_resource) as res:
 165         yield res
 166

 168 def is_resource(package: Package, name: str) -> bool:
 169     """True if `name` is a resource inside `package`.
 170 
 171     Directories are *not* resources.
 172     """
 173     package = _get_package(package)
 174     _normalize_path(name)
 175     reader = _get_resource_reader(package)
 176     if reader is not None:
 177         return reader.is_resource(name)
 178     package_contents = set(contents(package))
 179     if name not in package_contents:
 180         return False
 181     return (_common.from_package(package) / name).is_file()
 182 
 183 
 184 def contents(package: Package) -> Iterable[str]:
 185     """Return an iterable of entries in `package`.
 186 
 187     Note that not all entries are resources.  Specifically, directories are
 188     not considered resources.  Use `is_resource()` on each entry returned here
 189     to check if it is a resource or not.
 190     """
 191     package = _get_package(package)
 192     reader = _get_resource_reader(package)
 193     if reader is not None:
 194         return reader.contents()
 195     # Is the package a namespace package?  By definition, namespace packages
 196     # cannot have resources.
 197     namespace = (
 198         package.__spec__.origin is None or
 199         package.__spec__.origin == 'namespace'
 200         )
 201     if namespace or not package.__spec__.has_location:
 202         return ()
 203     return list(item.name for item in _common.from_package(package).iterdir())
